org.jpasecurity.jpql.compiler

Class QueryEvaluator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jpasecurity.jpql.parser.JpqlVisitorAdapter<QueryEvaluationParameters>
      • org.jpasecurity.jpql.compiler.QueryEvaluator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JpqlParserVisitor<QueryEvaluationParameters>

    public class QueryEvaluator
extends JpqlVisitorAdapter<QueryEvaluationParameters>
    This implementation of the JpqlVisitorAdapter evaluates queries in memory, storing the result in the specified QueryEvaluationParameters. If the evaluation cannot be performed due to missing information the result is set to undefined. To evaluate subselect-query, pluggable implementations of SubselectEvaluator are used.
    Author:
    Arne Limburg
